<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="486" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1436,976,1472]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1012,1037]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Comments.</emphasis>
This species is here transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1855" box="[835,977,1012,1036]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Microchrysa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[835,977,1012,1036]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Microchrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because it has a broad upper frons that is as wide as each eye, a postocular region that is well developed, vein M is not distinct throughout its length, and veins M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[242,250,1099,1113]" fontSize="6" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">1</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[329,337,1099,1113]" fontSize="6" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">3</subScript>
are very weakly developed, being much fainter than M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[957,965,1099,1113]" fontSize="6" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">2</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1044,1052,1099,1113]" fontSize="6" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">4</subScript>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1436,976,1472]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">
This species is bigger and darker than others known Neotropical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1855" box="[936,1078,1123,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Microchrysa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[936,1078,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Microchrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and it is less shiny, not having the green or blue metallic sheen on its head that is commonly seen in other Neotropical species such as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wiedemann, 1830)" authorityName="Wiedemann" authorityYear="1830" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1830" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Microchrysa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[1317,1436,1159,1183]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">M. bicolor</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wiedemann, C. R. W." box="[158,369,1195,1220]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" refId="ref22774" refString="Wiedemann, C. R. W. (1830) Aussereuropaische zweiflugelige Insekten. Zweiter Theil. Schulzischen Buchhandlung, Hamm, XII + 684 pp." type="book" year="1830">Wiedemann, 1830</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Only 
<taxonomicName authority=", McFadden in James &amp; McFadden, 1982" authorityName=", McFadden in James &amp; McFadden" authorityYear="1982" box="[452,1118,1195,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Microchrysa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscuriventris">
<emphasis box="[452,650,1195,1219]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">M. obscuriventris</emphasis>
, McFadden 
<emphasis box="[792,814,1196,1219]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">in</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="James, M. T. &amp; M. W. McFadden" box="[822,1118,1195,1220]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref22038" refString="James, M. T. &amp; M. W. McFadden. (1982) The Sarginae (Diptera: Stratiomyidae) of Middle America. Melanderia, 40, vii-x + 1 - 50." type="journal article" year="1982">James &amp; McFadden, 1982</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(examined) is as dark as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schiner, 1868)" authorityName="Fachin &amp; Hauser" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Schiner" baseAuthorityYear="1868" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Chrysonotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendens" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">M. splendens</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schiner, J. R." box="[276,433,1230,1255]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" refId="ref22626" refString="Schiner, J. R. (1868) Diptera. In: Reise der osterreichischen Fregatte Novara um die Erde in den Jahren 1857, 1858, 1859, unter den Befehlen des Commodore B. von Wullerstorf-Urbair. Zoologischer Theil 2. 1 (B). Kaiserlich-koniglichen Hof- und Staatsdruckeri in comission bei Karl Gerold's Sohn, Wien, pp. I-VI + 1 - 388. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 7913" type="journal volume" year="1868">Schiner, 1868</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[448,577,1230,1255]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[448,577,1230,1255]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", McFadden in James &amp; McFadden" authorityYear="1982" box="[662,860,1231,1255]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Microchrysa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscuriventris">
<emphasis box="[662,860,1231,1255]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">M. obscuriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the whole abdomen is completely dark brown with some metallic purple reflections, all legs are yellow and the discal cell slightly smaller, while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fachin &amp; Hauser" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Schiner" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[1284,1435,1267,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Chrysonotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendens" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1284,1435,1267,1291]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">M. splendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,1302,1327]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,281,1302,1327]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, the abdomen does not seem to be entirely dark dorsally, it has at least the last three hind tarsomeres dark brown and its discal cell is larger. The other five known species of 
<taxonomicName authority="in Neotropical" authorityName="in Neotropical" box="[958,1268,1339,1364]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Microchrysa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[958,1100,1339,1363]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Microchrysa</emphasis>
in Neotropical
</taxonomicName>
region need to be urgently revised.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1436,976,1472]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">
